{
  "doc_id": "31573",
  "text": "We have found that the entropy shift is always positive for this family of solutions. In previous works in the literature, it has been claimed that the positivity of the corrections to the entropy imply a positive correction to the charge-to-mass ratio at extremality [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . On the contrary, this claim has been disputed by the counterexample presented in Ref. [CITATION_4] , in which ∆S > 0 but ∆(q/M) = 0. It is interesting to ask what the situation is here, since we have a non-extremal solution at our disposal and we can perform a more detailed analysis. In Ref. [CITATION_5] the shifts are claimed to satisfy a universal relation,",
